Palp as in diagnosis. Retrolateral margin of cymbium slightly concave in distal half (ventral view,
Fig. 25
). Embolus short, arising from 10 -o’clock-position on tegulum, its tip pointing prolaterally. Rounded apophysis close to base of conductor. Sperm-duct running submarginally along retrolateral margin of tegulum (
Fig. 25
), bent in an angle at tegular bulge (prolateral view,
Fig. 24
