Fig. 25
), with indentation on base of ventral margin (retrolateral view,
Figs 26–27
), dorsal part forming a circle-shaped interspace with ventral part. Tip of ventral part slightly curved.

Copulatory organ as in diagnosis. Epigynal field clearly wider than long. Epigyne similar to P. s a e t o s a sp. n. Median margins of lateral lobes parallel and almost straight. Posterior margins with slight median indentation (
Fig. 29
). Space between fertilisation ducts and first winding smaller than width of first winding (
Fig. 30
). In one specimen, a subadult female, a pre-epigyne was present (
Fig. 31
). It is illustrated to avoid confusion of mature and immature females.

Distribution. Only known from the type locality and three localities not further than 10 air km away (localities 3-6 in
